SIMPLE: jager
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jager
<hw>Ja"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>j⟦aum⟧ger</ets> a hunter, a sportsman. Cf. <er>Yager</er>.]</ety>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>jaeger</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A sharpshooter. See <er>Yager</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species of gull of the genus
<gen>Stercorarius</gen>. Three species occur on the Atlantic coast. The
jagers pursue other species of gulls and force them to disgorge their
prey. The two middle tail feathers are usually decidedly longer than the
rest. Called also <altname>boatswain</altname>, and
<altname>marline-spike bird</altname>. The name is also applied to the
skua, or Arctic gull (<spn>Megalestris skua</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>jagg</ent>⟦br⟧
